        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 2:42PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 241 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Rutherfordton, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rutherfordton, Columbus, Forest City, Spindale, Mill Spring, Green
Creek, and Lake Adger.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
